and some blueberries.

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:55.907
What you're going to do is just

00:00:55.907 --> 00:00:57.643
put everything in your juicer.

00:00:57.643 --> 00:01:00.645
And so this is a weird technique

00:01:00.645 --> 00:01:03.048
that I learned from juicing many times,

00:01:03.048 --> 00:01:05.934
but what I do is because the spring mix

00:01:05.934 --> 00:01:08.724
and the spinach don't
have a lot of juice in it,

00:01:08.724 --> 00:01:11.391
what I do is first I'll
put that in, right?

00:01:13.151 --> 00:01:15.644
And I'll fill it in until
it's completely full.

00:01:16.327 --> 00:01:19.037
Or I feel that it's full.
So it's almost full, right?

00:01:19.037 --> 00:01:20.578
And then I'm going to add something

00:01:20.578 --> 00:01:23.296
that has a lot of juice,
like an Asian pear.

00:01:24.526 --> 00:01:26.508
And this will get more juice out of

00:01:26.508 --> 00:01:28.170
the spinach and the spring mix.

00:01:28.170 --> 00:01:30.214
So let's see how that goes.

00:01:31.663 --> 00:01:36.663
(juicer grinding)

00:01:43.021 --> 00:01:45.890
(juicer winding down)

00:01:45.890 --> 00:01:47.448
That's cool, huh?

00:01:51.162 --> 00:01:55.261
